main event: A woman in Crittenden, Kentucky observed a bright white object that was too large and too close to be a star on August 11, 1969.
interesting points: The object changed colors to pink and seemed to pulsate.
The observation lasted for approximately 20 minutes.
The observer reported the sighting to the Aerial Phenomena Office of the Department of the Air Force.
The Air Force requested additional data from the observer to investigate the sighting further.
The Air Force concluded the sighting was a 'Probable Astro (STARS/PLANETS)' and that there seemed to be no evidence the sighting could not have been of a star or planet.
sighted object: a bright white object, too large and too close to be a star, that changed colors to pink and seemed to pulsate
